    {
      "parameters": {
        "content": "## Watcher \u2014 Teams transcripts \u2192 inbox\nEvery 15 min: read the watchlist (allow-listed people) \u2192 pull each person's meeting transcripts in the last 35 min \u2192 dedupe by transcript id \u2192 drop into `inbox` (pending) \u2192 fire the Main Pipeline once per NEW call.\n\n**Edge case handled:** 2 calls \u2192 2 inbox rows \u2192 2 pipeline runs, each claims its own row (FOR UPDATE SKIP LOCKED). Transcripts never mix.",
        "height": 260,
        "width": 420
      },
      "id": "w_note1",
      "name": "How it works",
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote",
      "typeVersion": 1,
      "position": [
        0,
        -20
      ]
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "content": "## \u26a0\ufe0f Before going live \u2014 confirm 3 things\n1. **Credential 'MS Graph'** \u2014 Entra app with `OnlineMeetingTranscript.Read.All` (application) + an application access policy granting it. Select it on the 3 HTTP nodes.\n2. **Endpoints** \u2014 if your original working automation used different Graph URLs/params, paste it and I'll drop them in exactly.\n3. **Watchlist** \u2014 run `db/2026-07_watchlist.sql` and insert the real GUIDs/UPNs.\n\nThen pick the target workflow on 'Trigger pipeline'.",
        "height": 300,
        "width": 460
      },
